properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 6 at 7:58AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a Flood
Warning for the following rivers in Alabama...Florida...Georgia...

Pea River near Ariton (US 231) affecting Coffee and Dale Counties
Choctawhatchee River near Newton (SR 134) affecting Dale County
Choctawhatchee River near Caryville (US 90) affecting Holmes and
Washington Counties
Choctawhatchee River near Bruce (SR 20) affecting Walton and
Washington Counties
Kinchafoonee Creek near 11 E Of Dawson At Pinewood Rd In Lee County
affecting Lee County
Chipola River at Marianna (US 90) affecting Jackson County

The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a

* Flood Warning for
the Choctawhatchee River near Bruce (SR 20).
* From Sunday evening, or until the warning is cancelled.
* At  6:45 AM Thursday the stage was 8.9 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Flood stage is 14.0 feet.
* Forecast: Rise above flood stage by Sunday evening and continue to
rise to near 15.5 feet by early Tuesday morning. Additional rises
are possible thereafter.
* Impact: At 16.0 feet: Portions of Big Cedar, Cowford, and
Choctawhatchee River Roads in Walton County are impassible above
this level. Structures in the area not elevated begin flooding.
Portions of Choctaw Road in Washington County begin to flood along
with Strickland Road in the far southwestern portion of the county.
properties.instruction:
All persons with interest along the river should monitor the latest
forecasts, and be prepared to take necessary precautions to protect
life and property. Do not drive cars through flooded areas. If you
see flood waters: Turn around. Don't drown.

For graphical hydrologic information, please go to weather.gov and
click on your state. Select Rivers and Lakes AHPS under current
conditions and click on your river point.
